- **Latest Version**: Spring Cloud Stream 3.x, RabbitMQ 3.8.x
- **Key Config Options**:
  - `spring.cloud.stream.bindings.input.destination`: Specifies the name of the RabbitMQ queue for input.
  - `spring.cloud.stream.bindings.output.destination`: Specifies the name of the RabbitMQ queue for output.
  - `spring.rabbitmq.host`: The hostname or IP address of the RabbitMQ server.
  - `spring.rabbitmq.port`: The port number on which the RabbitMQ server is listening.
- **CLI Commands**:
  - `mvn clean install` to build your Spring Cloud Stream application.
  - `java -jar target/your-application.jar` to run your application.
- **Example Code Snippet**:
  ```java
  @EnableBinding(Sink.class)
  public class Receiver {
      @StreamListener(Sink.INPUT)
      public void receiveMessage(String message) {
          System.out.println("Received: " + message);
      }
  }
  ```
